#: GUI/app.py:190
msgid ""
"iOpenPod could not read this iPod cleanly.\n"
"\n"
"Mount path: {mount}\n"
"System error: {error}\n"
"\n"
"On Linux, this usually means the iPod mount is not accessible, the FAT filesystem is dirty, or the current user does not have permission to the mount.\n"
"\n"
"Try reconnecting the iPod. If it still fails, try remounting it read-write:\n"
"  sudo mount -o remount,rw {quoted_mount}\n"
"\n"
"If the filesystem is dirty, unmount it before repairing it:\n"
"  sudo umount {quoted_mount}\n"
"  sudo fsck.vfat -a /dev/sdXN\n"
"\n"
"Replace /dev/sdXN with the iPod partition. Do not run fsck while the iPod is mounted."
msgstr ""
"iOpenPod could not read this iPod cleanly.\n"
"\n"
"Mount path: {mount}\n"
"System error: {error}\n"
"\n"
"On Linux, this usually means the iPod mount is not accessible, the FAT filesystem is dirty, or the current user does not have permission to the mount.\n"
"\n"
"Try reconnecting the iPod. If it still fails, try remounting it read-write:\n"
"  sudo mount -o remount,rw {quoted_mount}\n"
"\n"
"If the filesystem is dirty, unmount it before repairing it:\n"
"  sudo umount {quoted_mount}\n"
"  sudo fsck.vfat -a /dev/sdXN\n"
"\n"
"Replace /dev/sdXN with the iPod partition. Do not run fsck while the iPod is mounted."

